  • public class DataSynchService
extends EntityCRUDService<DataSynchAction>
    This class can be used to create a bean data control to build your own UI to show pending sync actions. This class is also used by the reusable DataSynch feature.

      • getEntityListName

        protected java.lang.String getEntityListName()
        Description copied from class: EntityCRUDService
        This method returns the name of the property used to return the array of entity instances. This name is used to automatically send change notifcations when the list of entities has been changed so your mobile UI will automatically refresh. For example, if you have a method getDepartments, this method should return "departments"

      • dataSynchFinished

        protected void dataSynchFinished(java.util.List<DataSynchAction> succeededDataSynchActions,
                                 java.util.List<DataSynchAction> failedDataSynchActions)
        Callback method called by DataSynchronizer when dataSychronization action is done. It contains a list of succeeded and failed data sync actions. You can override this method to add custom logic after data synchronization has taken place. For example, you could warn the end user that one or more transactions have failed and will be re-tried later, or you can inform them that all pending data sync actions have been processed successfully.
        Overrides:
        dataSynchFinished in class EntityCRUDService<DataSynchAction>

        failedDataSynchActions -

      • removeDataSynchAction

        public void removeDataSynchAction(DataSynchAction dataSynchAction)
        This method is automatically called when using the Delete operation on the dataSynchAction collection in the data control palette. It removes the dataSynchAction instance passed in from the dataSynchAction list, deletes the corresponding row from the database. Do NOT drag and drop this method from the data control palette, use the Delete operation instead to ensure that iterator binding and dataSynchAction list stay in sync.
        Parameters:
        department -
